    "en": "Selenium is an essential micronutrient for good health. It is a component of the enzyme glutathione peroxidase, the metabolic role of which is to protect against oxidation of polyunsaturated fatty acids and resultant tissue damage, meaning it can counter the damage caused by free radicals. It is also important for the functioning of the thyroid gland.\n",
